### ============================================
### 4. METRICS — Check system observability
### ============================================

### 4.1 Full overview (throughput + status + errors + queues)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/overview

### 4.2 Throughput by source (last 60 minutes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/throughput

### 4.3 Throughput (custom window - last 5 minutes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/throughput?minutes=5

### 4.4 Latency stats (p50, p95, p99 by source)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/latency

### 4.5 Error rate and breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/errors

### 4.6 Error rate (last 5 minutes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/errors?minutes=5

### 4.7 Queue depths (BullMQ)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/queues

### 4.8 DLQ summary (dead events by source and error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/dlq


### ============================================
### 5. DLQ — Dead Letter Queue management
### ============================================

### 5.1 List dead events (default: limit=50)
GET {{baseUrl}}/dlq

### 5.2 List with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/dlq?source=stripe&limit=10

### 5.3 List with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/dlq?limit=5&offset=0

### 5.4 Get single DLQ event detail (replace with real ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/dlq/REPLACE_WITH_EVENT_ID

### 5.5 Discard single event (replace with real ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/dlq/REPLACE_WITH_EVENT_ID/discard

### 5.6 Batch discard (replace with real IDs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/dlq/discard
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": ["REPLACE_WITH_ID_1", "REPLACE_WITH_ID_2"]
}


### ============================================
### 6. ALERTS — Configure monitoring rules
### ============================================

### 6.1 Create alert: high error rate
POST {{baseUrl}}/alerts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "High Error Rate",
    "metric": "ERROR_RATE",
    "threshold": 10,
    "window": "5m",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "cooldown": "15m"
}

### 6.2 Create alert: queue backing up
POST {{baseUrl}}/alerts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Queue Backlog",
    "metric": "QUEUE_SIZE",
    "threshold": 100,
    "window": "1m",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "cooldown": "5m"
}

### 6.3 Create alert: too many dead events
POST {{baseUrl}}/alerts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "DLQ Growing",
    "metric": "DLQ_SIZE",
    "threshold": 5,
    "window": "10m",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "cooldown": "30m"
}

### 6.4 Create alert: high latency
POST {{baseUrl}}/alerts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "High Latency P95",
    "metric": "LATENCY_P95",
    "threshold": 5000,
    "window": "5m",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "cooldown": "10m"
}

### 6.5 Create alert: schema drift detected
POST {{baseUrl}}/alerts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Schema Drift",
    "metric": "SCHEMA_DRIFT",
    "threshold": 3,
    "window": "15m",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "cooldown": "1h"
}

### 6.6 List all alert rules
GET {{baseUrl}}/alerts

### 6.7 View alert firing history
GET {{baseUrl}}/alerts/history

### 6.8 View history for specific rule (replace with real ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/alerts/history?alertRuleId=REPLACE_WITH_RULE_ID&limit=20

### 6.9 Update alert threshold (replace with real ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/alerts/REPLACE_WITH_RULE_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "threshold": 20,
    "window": "10m"
}

### 6.10 Deactivate alert (replace with real ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/alerts/REPLACE_WITH_RULE_ID


### ============================================
### 7. REPLAY — Re-process failed events
### ============================================

### 7.1 Preview: how many FAILED events from stripe?
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/preview
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "FAILED"
}

### 7.2 Preview: all DEAD events
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/preview
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterStatus": "DEAD"
}

### 7.3 Preview: failed events in a time range
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/preview
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "FAILED",
    "filterFrom": "2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    "filterTo": "2030-12-31T23:59:59.999Z"
}

### 7.4 Execute replay (async — returns 202)
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "FAILED",
    "requestedBy": "admin"
}

### 7.5 List replay history
GET {{baseUrl}}/replay/history

### 7.6 Check replay status/progress (replace with real ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/replay/REPLACE_WITH_REPLAY_ID

### 7.7 Cancel a running replay (replace with real ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/REPLACE_WITH_REPLAY_ID/cancel


