### ============================================
### 9. SCHEMA MANAGEMENT — Update & deactivate
### ============================================

### 9.1 Update schema to strict mode (replace with real ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/schemas/REPLACE_WITH_SCHEMA_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "rejectOnFail": true
}

### 9.2 Deactivate schema (replace with real ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/schemas/REPLACE_WITH_SCHEMA_ID


### ============================================
### 10. E2E SCENARIO — Full payment flow
###     Simulates: Stripe → Topaz → process → check
### ============================================

### 10.1 Send payment event
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "evt_e2e_001",
    "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "data": {
        "object": {
            "id": "pi_e2e_001",
            "amount": 49990,
            "currency": "brl",
            "status": "succeeded",
            "customer": "cus_abc123",
            "metadata": {
                "order_id": "ORD-2024-001",
                "product": "Premium Plan"
            }
        }
    }
}

### 10.2 Check it arrived in metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/overview

### 10.3 Check queue stats (should show processing)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/queues

### 10.4 Send a payment that will fail validation (strict schema)
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "evt_e2e_002",
    "type": "charge.refunded",
    "data": {
        "wrong_field": "this should be rejected"
    }
}

### 10.5 Verify the invalid event was rejected (should return 400)
### Previous request ↑ should already show the 400 response

### 10.6 Check for schema drift in metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/errors


### ============================================
### 11. REPLAY TESTING — Create failed events & replay them
### ============================================

### 11.1 Send events that will FAIL (for replay testing)
### These events have "_testFail": true in the payload
### After 3 retry attempts, they become FAILED/DEAD
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "evt_fail_001",
    "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "_testFail": true,
    "data": {
        "object": {
            "id": "pi_fail_001",
            "amount": 9990,
            "currency": "brl",
            "status": "succeeded"
        }
    }
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "evt_fail_002",
    "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "_testFail": true,
    "data": {
        "object": {
            "id": "pi_fail_002",
            "amount": 15000,
            "currency": "usd",
            "status": "succeeded"
        }
    }
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/stripe
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "evt_fail_003",
    "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "_testFail": true,
    "data": {
        "object": {
            "id": "pi_fail_003",
            "amount": 5000,
            "currency": "brl",
            "status": "succeeded"
        }
    }
}

### 11.2 Wait ~30 seconds for retries to complete, then check DLQ
### Events should appear as FAILED/DEAD after all retry attempts
GET {{baseUrl}}/dlq?source=stripe&limit=10

### 11.3 Check metrics to see failed events
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics/overview

### 11.4 Preview replay: how many FAILED events from stripe?
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/preview
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "FAILED"
}

### 11.5 Preview replay: DEAD events
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/preview
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "DEAD"
}

### 11.6 Execute replay of FAILED events
### This will re-enqueue all FAILED events from stripe
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterSource": "stripe",
    "filterStatus": "FAILED",
    "requestedBy": "test-admin"
}

### 11.7 Execute replay of DEAD events (all sources)
POST {{baseUrl}}/replay/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "filterStatus": "DEAD",
    "requestedBy": "test-admin"
}

### 11.8 Check replay history
GET {{baseUrl}}/replay/history

### 11.9 Check specific replay status (replace ID from 11.6 or 11.7 response)
### GET {{baseUrl}}/replay/REPLACE_REPLAY_ID


### ============================================
### 12. ROUTES — Configure event routing (fan-out)
### ============================================

### 12.1 Create a route (single target)
POST {{baseUrl}}/routes
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "source": "stripe",
    "eventType": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "targetName": "payment-processor",
    "method": "POST",
    "timeout": 5000,
    "retryCount": 3,
    "priority": "CRITICAL"
}

### 12.2 Create another route for same event (fan-out)
POST {{baseUrl}}/routes
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "source": "stripe",
    "eventType": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "targetName": "slack-notifications",
    "method": "POST",
    "timeout": 3000,
    "retryCount": 1,
    "priority": "LOW"
}

### 12.3 Create catch-all route (wildcard event type)
POST {{baseUrl}}/routes
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "source": "stripe",
    "eventType": "*",
    "targetUrl": "https://httpbin.org/post",
    "targetName": "stripe-catchall",
    "method": "POST",
    "timeout": 10000,
    "priority": "NORMAL"
}

### 12.4 List all routes
GET {{baseUrl}}/routes

### 12.5 List routes by source
GET {{baseUrl}}/routes/source/stripe

### 12.6 Update route timeout (replace with real ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/routes/REPLACE_WITH_ROUTE_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "timeout": 10000,
    "retryCount": 5
}

### 12.7 Deactivate route (replace with real ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/routes/REPLACE_WITH_ROUTE_ID

### 12.8 Permanently delete route (replace with real ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/routes/REPLACE_WITH_ROUTE_ID/permanent
